Subject: Re: [T2] Points lubrication

> "Deltano, Jeffrey L" <jeffrey.l.deltano(-at-)intel.com> wrote:
>   Hi All,
>
> I recently replaced the points in my 81 vanagon westy. The points did
> not come with the little capsule of grease like they used to, and I am
> sorry to say that I forgot to put some on them after installing and
> timing the engine. By the end of my camping trip they were toast, the
> engine would break up if I tried to rev to high and had lousy
> acceleration. What kind of lubrication should I use when I install the
> next set?

A good VWFLAPS will carry Bosch distributor point grease in a little
yellow and black tube.  One tube will last a very long time.  The grease
is very thick and stays put on the cam.  I also use it for clutch pilot
bearings.

George
